  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated remorse by making partial restitution. A 10-year sentence suggested by the spectator is disproportionately punitive and inconsistent with standard sentencing guidelines for this offense level. Given the mitigating factors of a clean criminal record and partial repayment, a period of 6 months of incarceration combined with a probationary period and full restitution is deemed an appropriate, proportional response to maintain justice while accounting for rehabilitation.",
